quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  25,68,"who do not invoke any other god besides Allah, nor kill any soul which Allah has made sacred, except for a just cause, nor commit fornication - he that does this shall be punished for his sin"
  25,69,and his punishment shall be doubled on the Day of Resurrection and in disgrace he shall abide forever
  25,70,"except the one who repents, becomes a true believer, and starts doing good deeds, for then Allah will change his evil deeds into good, and Allah is Most Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  25,71,"He that repents and does good deeds, has truly turned to Allah with good turning"
  25,72,"Those are the ones who do not bear witness to falsehood and, if they ever pass by futility, pass with dignity"
  25,73,"Who, when reminded about the revelations of their Lord, do not turn a blind eye and a deaf ear to them"
  25,74,"Who pray: \"Our Lord! Make our wives and our children to be the comfort of our eyes, and make us leaders of the righteous"
  25,75,"Such are the ones who will be rewarded with the lofty places in paradise for their patience, wherein they shall be welcomed with greetings and salutations"
  25,76,They shall live forever in that excellent dwelling and excellent resting place
  25,77,"O Muhammad! Say: \"My Lord does not care at all if you invoke Him or not. Now that you have rejected His revelations, soon you will face the inevitable punishment"